-- Toronto-Dominion Sets $1.6 Billion Profit Target for U.S. Consumer Bank
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-06-16T14:52:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-16/toronto-dominion-sets-1-6-billion-profit-target-for-u-s-consumer-bank.html

          
          
             Toronto-Dominion Bank , Canada’s
second-largest bank, set a profit target of $1.6 billion for its
U.S. consumer-lending business within three years, according to
a presentation to investors today.  
 For the fiscal year that ended Oct. 31, the Toronto-based
bank earned $781 million in adjusted profit from the U.S.
segment, according to the  presentation . Toronto-Dominion plans
to meet with investors in New York today.  
 The profit growth over the next three years will be driven
by acquisitions, branch expansion and reduced loan losses,
according to the presentation on the bank’s website.  
